<article>
  <div class="kicker">An essay on social infrastructure</div>
  <h1 class="title">Shared Rituals, <em>Real Trust</em>.</h1>
  <p class="dek">Most communities don't need enterprise software. They need tools that respect the shape of how they already live.</p>
  <div class="byline">
    <span><strong>Vibes DIY</strong> · field notes</span>
    <span>illustrated with apps from our community</span>
  </div>

  <p class="lede">There was a moment in the early internet when software felt different.</p>

  <div class="stanza">
    <p class="tight">Not smarter.</p>
    <p class="tight">Not more optimized.</p>
    <p class="tight"><em>More human.</em></p>
  </div>

  <p>People stayed in strangers' homes through Airbnb.</p>
  <p>They edited Wikipedia with no expectation of ownership.</p>
  <p>They hosted each other on couches.</p>
  <p>They uploaded weird music.</p>
  <p>They ran forums for obscure hobbies.</p>
  <p>They built open-source software with people they had never met.</p>

  <p>This was not because the technology was advanced.</p>

  <p>It was because the <em>social boundary</em> was still visible.</p>

  <p>The people using these systems felt:</p>

  <ul class="prose-list">
    <li>culturally aligned</li>
    <li>experimentally minded</li>
    <li>mutually legible</li>
    <li>part of the same horizon</li>
  </ul>

  <p>The software did not create trust from nothing.</p>

  <blockquote class="pull">It <span class="em">amplified</span> trust that already existed.</blockquote>

  <p>Over time, the internet became optimized for scale instead of scenes. Platforms stopped feeling like places where communities coordinated themselves and started feeling like feeds competing for attention.</p>

  <p>The result was software that became very good at engagement and very bad at belonging.</p>

  <div class="ornament">· · ·</div>

  <h2 class="section-head">But underneath all of this, people <em>never stopped</em> organizing themselves.</h2>

  <p>House show networks still route touring bands through cities.</p>

  <figure class="app">
    <a class="shot" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/crooked-cricket-2926">
      <img
        src="https://crooked-cricket-2926--og.prod-v2.vibesdiy.net/screenshot.jpg"
        alt="Toronto Pride event finder"
        onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='{{assetPrefix}}images/og-preview.png';">
    </a>
    <figcaption>
      <div class="label">Scenes that route themselves</div>
      <h3>Event Finder for a City's Scene</h3>
      <p>Searches the open web for parades, parties, and shows in a city, then saves them to a shared calendar. The scene already exists — the app just learns to read it.</p>
      <div class="links">
        <a class="primary" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/crooked-cricket-2926">Visit</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/crooked-cricket-2926?skipChat=true">Clone</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/crooked-cricket-2926">Remix</a>
      </div>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>Parents still coordinate carpools.</p>

  <p>Restaurants still swap shifts in group chats.</p>

  <figure class="app">
    <a class="shot" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/shift-cash-board">
      <img
        src="https://shift-cash-board--og.prod-v2.vibesdiy.net/screenshot.jpg"
        alt="End-of-shift cash and tip reconciliation board"
        onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='{{assetPrefix}}images/og-preview.png';">
    </a>
    <figcaption>
      <div class="label">Trust at shift change</div>
      <h3>End-of-Shift Cash &amp; Tip Board</h3>
      <p>Closers enter cash, card total, tip pool, voids. The app flags discrepancies and stores a per-closer sign-off. The handoff already happens — the app gives it memory.</p>
      <div class="links">
        <a class="primary" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/shift-cash-board">Visit</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/shift-cash-board?skipChat=true">Clone</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/shift-cash-board">Remix</a>
      </div>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>Neighborhoods still improvise mutual aid during storms.</p>

  <figure class="app">
    <a class="shot" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/ancient-echo-1713">
      <img
        src="https://ancient-echo-1713--og.prod-v2.vibesdiy.net/screenshot.jpg"
        alt="Shelter, food bank, and transit help directory"
        onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='{{assetPrefix}}images/og-preview.png';">
    </a>
    <figcaption>
      <div class="label">Mutual aid, made legible</div>
      <h3>Shelter &amp; Food Bank Finder</h3>
      <p>A bilingual directory of shelters, food banks, and transit help — with offline mode and a QR share. Built so the people doing the work can hand it to anyone, anywhere.</p>
      <div class="links">
        <a class="primary" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/ancient-echo-1713">Visit</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/ancient-echo-1713?skipChat=true">Clone</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/ancient-echo-1713">Remix</a>
      </div>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>Friends still run trips, events, projects, rituals, clubs, scenes, and subcultures through spreadsheets and text threads.</p>

  <figure class="app">
    <a class="shot" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/potluck-signup-board">
      <img
        src="https://potluck-signup-board--og.prod-v2.vibesdiy.net/screenshot.jpg"
        alt="Potluck signup board"
        onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='{{assetPrefix}}images/og-preview.png';">
    </a>
    <figcaption>
      <div class="label">The spreadsheet, redrawn</div>
      <h3>Potluck Signup Board</h3>
      <p>Who's bringing what, with dietary tags and a button to claim a missing category. The ritual is older than the internet. The board just stops the duplicate desserts.</p>
      <div class="links">
        <a class="primary" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/potluck-signup-board">Visit</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/potluck-signup-board?skipChat=true">Clone</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/potluck-signup-board">Remix</a>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:0.88rem; font-style:italic; color:var(--ink-faint); margin-top:0.5rem;">Clone this and describe your version — monthly book club, camping trip, holiday party — the shape is the&nbsp;same.</p>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <blockquote class="pull">The coordination <span class="em">already exists</span>.<br>The software just rarely respects its shape.</blockquote>

  <div class="ornament">· · ·</div>

  <h2 class="section-head">Most tools assume <em>the wrong shape</em>.</h2>

  <p>Most tools assume:</p>

  <ul class="prose-list">
    <li>hierarchy</li>
    <li>scale</li>
    <li>monetization</li>
    <li>formal process</li>
    <li>endless onboarding</li>
    <li>account trees</li>
    <li>dashboards</li>
  </ul>

  <p>But many real communities operate differently.</p>

  <p>They run on:</p>

  <ul class="prose-list">
    <li>trust</li>
    <li>reputation</li>
    <li>repeated interaction</li>
    <li>lightweight norms</li>
    <li>shared context</li>
    <li>recurring rituals</li>
  </ul>

  <figure class="app">
    <a class="shot" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/holiday-card-roster">
      <img
        src="https://holiday-card-roster--og.prod-v2.vibesdiy.net/screenshot.jpg"
        alt="Holiday card roster, year over year"
        onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='{{assetPrefix}}images/og-preview.png';">
    </a>
    <figcaption>
      <div class="label">Memory across years</div>
      <h3>Holiday Card Roster</h3>
      <p>Per-year columns of sent, received, skipped. A small artifact of a household's repeated interaction — the kind of memory most software forgets.</p>
      <div class="links">
        <a class="primary" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/holiday-card-roster">Visit</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/holiday-card-roster?skipChat=true">Clone</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/holiday-card-roster">Remix</a>
      </div>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>These groups do not need enterprise software.</p>

  <p>They need <em>social infrastructure</em>.</p>

  <div class="stanza">
    <p class="tight">Not social media.</p>
    <p class="tight"><em>Social infrastructure.</em></p>
  </div>

  <p>That distinction matters.</p>

  <blockquote class="pull">
    Social media <span class="em">extracts</span> attention from communities.<br>
    Social infrastructure <span class="em">strengthens</span> communities.
  </blockquote>

  <p>One turns people into audiences.</p>

  <p>The other helps them coordinate their lives together.</p>

  <div class="ornament">· · ·</div>

  <h2 class="section-head">Why we care about <em>collaboration signals</em>, not clicks.</h2>

  <p>A click tells you:</p>

  <p style="font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.5rem; border-left: 2px solid var(--ember); color: var(--ink-soft);">"someone was curious."</p>

  <p>A share tells you:</p>

  <p style="font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.5rem; border-left: 2px solid var(--ember); color: var(--ink-soft);">"someone saw themselves and their people in this."</p>

  <p>That is a much deeper signal.</p>

  <p>When someone immediately invites collaborators into a tool, something important is happening:</p>

  <ul class="prose-list">
    <li>the workflow is real</li>
    <li>the trust network already exists</li>
    <li>the software fits the social shape</li>
    <li>the ritual wants infrastructure</li>
  </ul>

  <figure class="app">
    <a class="shot" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/seder-run-of-show">
      <img
        src="https://seder-run-of-show--og.prod-v2.vibesdiy.net/screenshot.jpg"
        alt="Holiday-host run-of-show checklist"
        onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='{{assetPrefix}}images/og-preview.png';">
    </a>
    <figcaption>
      <div class="label">A ritual wants infrastructure</div>
      <h3>Seder Run-of-Show</h3>
      <p>Ordered steps with times and notes — when each dish goes in, who reads which passage — saved as a reusable template for next year. The host already knows the shape. The app just remembers it.</p>
      <div class="links">
        <a class="primary" href="https://vibes.diy/vibe/og/seder-run-of-show">Visit</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/seder-run-of-show?skipChat=true">Clone</a>
        <a href="https://vibes.diy/remix/og/seder-run-of-show">Remix</a>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:0.88rem; font-style:italic; color:var(--ink-faint); margin-top:0.5rem;">Clone it and describe your ritual — Thanksgiving, Diwali dinner, quarterly family reunion — the structure holds for any recurring&nbsp;event.</p>
    </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="ornament">· · ·</div>

  <h2 class="section-head">Invisible institutions, <em>waiting to become legible</em> to themselves.</h2>

  <p>The internet is full of invisible institutions waiting to become legible to themselves.</p>

  <p>Every scene already has:</p>

  <ul class="prose-list">
    <li>memory</li>
    <li>rituals</li>
    <li>coordination patterns</li>
    <li>identity</li>
    <li>governance</li>
    <li>trust</li>
  </ul>

  <p>What they often lack is software that feels native to the way they already live.</p>

  <p>That is the opportunity now.</p>

  <p>Not building software for <em>"users."</em></p>

  <p>Building software for <em>scenes</em>.</p>

  <blockquote class="pull">
    <span class="em">Shared rituals.</span> <span class="em">Real trust.</span>
  </blockquote>
</article>

